  "output": "The **color of the sky** is generally described as **blue**.\n\nThis phenomenon, known as **atmospheric refraction**, occurs because sunlight (or moonlight) passes through Earth's thick layer of air. As light travels through this atmosphere, it bends around particles like dust and water droplets, making the sky appear blue to our eyes. This effect is most noticeable when looking at stars near the horizon; if you see a bright spot in the night sky that looks like a star, it is likely one of these refracted rays.",
